column5: Does anyone out there have or have used an Sub Zero Ice Storm33 by Eskimo. It is an 8in power auger 1.2hp 33cc motor. I just picked one up at CanTire for half off. Not sure if its a piece of junk or not. Thanks in advance. By the way there were lots of Nautilus and Mustang floater coats still left, half price.
I'm sure it'll do the trick. The 33cc might be a little weak but take your time and with sharp blades it'll do its job. Better then hand drilling them.
Just add on a nitrous kit or a turbocharger and she'll be good to go.
I can sell you the NO2.....My buddy bought one a few weeks back and it works well.
